	<p>
		I'm <strong>Reza Shahabian</strong> (publishing as Mohamad Reza Shahabian Alashti), an
		<strong>AI engineer</strong> who builds <strong>agentic, multimodal AI systems end-to-end</strong> —
		from sensor data and models through evaluation to real-time deployment. I hold a
		<strong>PhD in Computer Science</strong> and currently work as a Research Fellow at the
		<strong>University of Hertfordshire</strong>, where my recent work centres on
		<strong>agentic AI</strong> (tool-using LLM workflows and the Model Context Protocol),
		<strong>vision–language models</strong>, and <strong>multimodal sensor fusion</strong> for
		healthcare and assistive robotics.
	</p>

	<p>
		What makes my background unusual is that it's <strong>vertically integrated</strong>. Before
		research I spent years shipping real systems: I led the design and delivery of integrated
		hardware–software infrastructure-monitoring platforms deployed across
		<strong>60+ data centres</strong>, and I led an electronics/robotics group whose teams won the
		IranOpen <strong>@Home league five times</strong> and competed at international RoboCup. So I
		don't just train models — I've owned products from concept to deployment, led cross-functional
		teams, and debugged systems in the field.
	</p>

	<p>
		On the research side, I've published <strong>20+ papers</strong> (ICRA, ICSR, BioRob and others)
		with <strong>67 citations</strong> and an <strong>h-index of 5</strong>, and I co-created the
		publicly available <strong>RHM-HAR multi-view datasets</strong> used by other researchers. My
		2026 work spans agentic human-activity recognition, zero-/few-shot vision–language fall
		detection, and multimodal intent detection for wearable assistive robotics.
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>What I'm looking for:</strong> applied AI / AI engineering roles where I can build and
		ship — agentic AI, LLM products, and multimodal ML — ideally at UK startups, scaleups, or
		research-driven product teams. I hold a <strong>UK Global Talent visa</strong> (endorsed by the
		Royal Academy of Engineering), so I require <strong>no visa sponsorship</strong>.
	</p>

